<field name="name">

&lt;P&gt;
atan2 - arctangent of 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;Y/X&lt;/FONT&gt; 

&lt;P&gt;
&lt;HR&gt;
</field>
<field name="synopsis">

&lt;P&gt;
atan2 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;Y,X&lt;/FONT&gt;

&lt;P&gt;
&lt;HR&gt;
</field>
<field name="description">

&lt;P&gt;
Returns the arctangent of 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;Y/X&lt;/FONT&gt; in the range 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;-PI&lt;/FONT&gt; to 
&lt;FONT SIZE=-1&gt;PI.&lt;/FONT&gt;

&lt;P&gt;
For the tangent operation, you may use the &lt;CODE&gt;POSIX::tan()&lt;/CODE&gt;
function, or use the familiar relation:

&lt;P&gt;
&lt;PRE&gt;    sub tan { sin($_&amp;#091;0&amp;#093;) / cos($_&amp;#091;0&amp;#093;)  }
&lt;/PRE&gt;
&lt;HR&gt;
</field>
